name: Cd2+-exporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + Cd2+in = ADP + phosphate + Cd2+out [RN:R00086]
comment: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. This enzyme occurs in protozoa, fungi and plants.

references.title: Newer systems for bacterial resistances to toxic heavy metals.
Formation of a phosphorylated enzyme intermediate by the cadA Cd(2+)-ATPase.
